            I should like to apologise to the Committee. The speaking notes I have been given are completely out of order and the last paragraph was complete gibberish! I was amazed that no one picked it up, but it did not relate to what I was meant to be saying. I sincerely apologise.</p><p>
            I wanted to give an example of where dual placements had worked. Beaumont Hill School and Technology College in Darlington&#x2014;a special school&#x2014;has done pioneering work in this area. The video I mentioned earlier shows how pupils can flourish by using dual placements. I reiterate what I said at the beginning; namely, we do not think that there is any reason to change primary legislation where something is already operating in exactly the way that the noble Baroness would wish. I hope that the noble Baroness will accept that the Government are absolutely committed to this measure and that it is already provided for.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0621P0-01225'>
        <a name='S5LV0621P0_20010123_GCR_73'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-brian-rix' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0621P0_20010123_GCR_73' title='Link to this speech by Mr Brian Rix' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
